 <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3">Peak Season Surcharges</h3>
 <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Pre-holiday peak (August through October) typically pushes ocean rates 20-40% above off-peak. Q4 inventory restocking causes the same spike for trans-Pacific routes. Planning your production calendar around these windows can reduce annual logistics costs by 10-15%, particularly for retail-bound seasonal SKUs. Our <a href="/blog/shipping-from-china-guide" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-bold">shipping from China guide</a> covers Incoterms, rate negotiation, and forwarder selection in detail.</p>
